A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a frustrated office worker surrounded by towering stacks of filing cabinets and manila folders, some drawers hanging open with papers spilling out chaotically. One cabinet stands pristine and orderly while another identical one beside it overflows with tangled documents creating a paper avalanche. The worker scratches their head while examining two nearly identical folder tabs, trying to determine which is the original. Warm sepia and cream tones with pops of mustard yellow and burnt orange, crosshatch shading technique reminiscent of mid-century technical manuals. A single desk lamp casts dramatic shadows across the scene, emphasizing the detective-like nature of troubleshooting duplicate data stores.
